-- GM says 2011 China auto sales up 8.3 percent on year
-- 
-- Sun Jan 8, 2012 10:14pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/01/09/us-gm-china-autos-idUSTRE80804Q20120109

 

 BEIJING  (Reuters) - General Motors ( GM.N ) and its joint ventures sold 2.55 million vehicles in China in 2011, up 8.3 percent from a year earlier, the U.S. automaker said on Monday. 
 Sales came to 196,797 vehicles in December, up 9.8 percent from a year earlier, it said in a statement. GM, the largest overseas automaker in China, operates auto manufacturing ventures in the country with SAIC Motor ( 600104.SS ) and FAW Group. (Reporting by Fang Yan and  Ken Wills )